Standardizing¶

We center and scale...we calculate the z-score.

In [10]:
penguins.body_mass_g.mean()
Out[10]:
4201.754385964912
In [11]:
penguins.body_mass_g.std()
Out[11]:
801.9545356980954

The z-score is the value minus the average divided by the standard deviation.

In [55]:
tots_within = []

K = range(1, 26)

for k in K:
    km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=121, n_init=25, max_iter=500)
    km = km.fit(X)
    tots_within.append(km.inertia_)
